WEBVTT

00:04.047 --> 00:06.310
- Yes, I know
you've been calling.

00:06.354 --> 00:09.052
I just--I haven't had time
to schedule a follow-up.

00:09.096 --> 00:10.445
Understood, Dr. Eli,

00:10.488 --> 00:12.708
but I have no plans
to get pregnant again, so...

00:12.751 --> 00:14.188
I'm at work.
I have to call you back.

00:14.231 --> 00:16.320
Is that all right? Thanks.
- Everything all right?

00:16.364 --> 00:17.495
- Yeah, just a thing
I'm pushing.

00:17.539 --> 00:18.844
- You just missed
our bud Barkey again.

00:18.888 --> 00:20.324
He dropped the price 5K.

00:20.368 --> 00:22.065
- Adam, what are you actually
gonna do with a boat?

00:22.109 --> 00:23.501
- I don't know,
sail the seven seas,

00:23.545 --> 00:24.633
become a new man.

00:24.676 --> 00:26.156
Park it in my garage,
drink beer on it.

00:26.200 --> 00:28.158
- Exactly, kind of boat
Barkey's gonna sell you,

00:28.202 --> 00:29.377
garage is a lot more likely.

00:29.420 --> 00:31.509
[both laugh]
- Anyway, I'm just saying...

00:31.553 --> 00:34.077
- Yeah?
- The change is good, you know?

00:34.121 --> 00:36.427
Like, for instance,
you and I, we don't date,

00:36.471 --> 00:40.736
and yet somehow we've become
my Gammie and Pawpaw.

00:40.779 --> 00:42.129
- You still call them that?

00:42.172 --> 00:44.827
- Well, that is their name.
- [laughs]

00:44.870 --> 00:46.872
- We go to the same diner
every morning.

00:46.916 --> 00:49.310
We go to work.
We go to the same bar.

00:49.353 --> 00:52.356
We do nothing new.
We go nowhere new.

00:52.400 --> 00:54.228
We meet nobody, date nobody.

00:54.271 --> 00:56.317
- We have no boat.
- See?

00:56.360 --> 00:57.535
Exactly.
- Mm-hmm.

00:57.579 --> 00:58.841
- This is what
I'm talking about.

00:58.884 --> 01:00.538
See, you're even
finishing my thoughts here.

01:00.582 --> 01:02.149
- Change is overrated, Adam.

01:02.192 --> 01:04.586
The whole world's looking for
a little same old right now.

01:04.629 --> 01:07.328
- Yeah, not guys
like me and Barkey.

01:07.371 --> 01:08.851
- [laughs]
No.

01:08.894 --> 01:11.201
You and Barkey are a set of
real revolutionary thinkers--

01:11.245 --> 01:12.376
- Yeah, exactly.
- Mm-hmm.

01:12.420 --> 01:13.508
- Yeah, I'm an adventurer.
- Of course.

01:13.551 --> 01:14.596
- I'm like a Renaissance man
over here.

01:14.639 --> 01:15.597
- You are, mm-hmm.

01:15.640 --> 01:16.859
[tires squealing]
Adam!

01:16.902 --> 01:18.861
[car horn blares]

01:18.904 --> 01:20.515
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:20.558 --> 01:23.518
Whoa, whoa.
Oh, my God.

01:23.561 --> 01:24.606
Hey! Hey, hey, hey!
- Get out of the road, kid!

01:24.649 --> 01:25.650
- Stay in your car.
Stay in your car.

01:25.694 --> 01:26.825
- Is she alone?
- Close your door.

01:26.869 --> 01:28.000
- Hey, hey, kiddo.
- Where's her family?

01:28.044 --> 01:29.132
- Hey, hey, hey, hey.
- It's all right.

01:29.176 --> 01:30.220
- It's okay.
It's okay.

01:30.264 --> 01:31.700
Let's get you out
of the street, okay?

01:31.743 --> 01:33.397
Where's your family?

01:33.441 --> 01:36.487
What are you doing around here?
Do you live around here?

01:36.531 --> 01:38.750
Did you run from someplace?
- All right, keep moving.

01:38.794 --> 01:41.144
- Are you lost, honey?

01:41.188 --> 01:42.754
There.
Do you live right there?

01:42.798 --> 01:44.495
Is that where you live?

01:44.539 --> 01:46.106
Are you lost?

01:47.933 --> 01:49.283
She's not talking.

01:50.849 --> 01:52.764
- There's nobody out here.
I mean, there's nobody around.

01:52.808 --> 01:54.462
- Where's your family?
Do you know?

01:55.811 --> 01:57.421
Okay, let's start again.
I'm Kim.

01:57.465 --> 01:59.336
This is Adam.
And we're police, see?

01:59.380 --> 02:00.598
That's what that star means.

02:00.642 --> 02:02.383
I'm a police officer.
I'm gonna help you.

02:02.426 --> 02:04.341
Okay?
I promise.

02:04.385 --> 02:06.865
- Yeah, this is Officer
Adam Ruzek, Intelligence.

02:06.909 --> 02:09.346
Recovered a tender age child...
- I like your outfit.

02:09.390 --> 02:11.435
Could I check something
really quickly?

02:11.479 --> 02:14.438
Just--I'm just gonna...
really fast.

02:14.482 --> 02:17.180
Adam?
- One sec.

02:17.224 --> 02:18.268
- Makayla Ward.

02:18.312 --> 02:19.922
- Yeah, I got a name.
- It's okay.

02:19.965 --> 02:22.403
Everything is gonna be okay,
all right?

02:22.446 --> 02:29.453
<i>♪</i>

02:34.719 --> 02:36.634
<i>Public school system
has the mom listed</i>

02:36.678 --> 02:37.853
<i>as Gabrielle Ward.</i>

02:37.896 --> 02:39.855
<i>4818 should be--
- Over there?</i>

02:39.898 --> 02:41.900
<i>- Yeah, there it is.</i>

02:41.944 --> 02:43.467
She's sleeping.

02:43.511 --> 02:46.209
I'll have the parents come out.
- Yeah.

02:46.253 --> 02:47.471
- Soft door.
Don't wake her up.

02:47.515 --> 02:49.604
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.
- All right.

02:49.647 --> 02:51.301
[chuckles]

03:02.747 --> 03:04.184
[knocking]

03:08.362 --> 03:10.668
<i>[sinister music]</i>

03:10.712 --> 03:13.584
- 5021 Eddie, requesting backup
at 4818 South Wells.

03:13.628 --> 03:16.761
<i>- Copy that, 5021 Eddie.
Backup on the way.</i>

03:16.805 --> 03:17.893
- What's going on?

03:17.936 --> 03:19.329
- There's blood splatter,
a lot of it.

03:19.373 --> 03:24.552
<i>♪</i>

03:24.595 --> 03:25.857
Ready?

03:27.598 --> 03:28.686
- Ah, it's open.

03:28.730 --> 03:30.949
- All right.

03:30.993 --> 03:34.039
One, two, three.

03:34.083 --> 03:39.262
<i>♪</i>

03:39.306 --> 03:40.524
Cover me.
- Yup.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.265
- Cover, cover, cover.

03:42.309 --> 03:44.267
- Body.
- Gotcha.

03:44.311 --> 03:51.274
<i>♪</i>

03:51.318 --> 03:52.623
- Clear.

03:52.667 --> 03:54.712
- I got another body.

03:54.756 --> 04:01.719
<i>♪</i>

04:01.763 --> 04:02.720
[door bangs shut]

04:02.764 --> 04:03.765
- You hear that?
- Yeah.

04:07.508 --> 04:09.814
[door creaks]

04:14.950 --> 04:16.386
[door bangs shut]

04:16.430 --> 04:17.822
- The back door.

04:20.608 --> 04:22.740
[door creaks]

04:22.784 --> 04:25.090
Backyard's clear.

04:25.134 --> 04:26.570
- [sighs]

04:26.614 --> 04:31.445
<i>♪</i>

04:31.488 --> 04:32.794
Adam.

04:36.754 --> 04:38.582
Look at these
little footprints.

04:38.626 --> 04:40.497
That little girl, Makayla,
she was here.

04:43.718 --> 04:44.980
- All right.
Call it in.

04:45.023 --> 04:46.677
I'm gonna go check on her.

04:46.721 --> 04:49.680
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

04:49.724 --> 04:56.731
<i>♪</i>

04:57.862 --> 04:59.951
- Burgess took the girl to Med.
They're checking her out.

04:59.995 --> 05:01.126
- Witnesses?
- Not yet.

05:01.170 --> 05:02.693
We're working the block.

05:02.737 --> 05:04.347
- ID the victims?

05:04.391 --> 05:06.567
- So they're all members
of the same family, the Wards.

05:06.610 --> 05:07.742
They all live in the house.

05:07.785 --> 05:09.091
And the little girl, Makayla?
- Uh-huh.

05:09.134 --> 05:11.789
- She's the only family member
that survived.

05:11.833 --> 05:14.749
- All right, let's keep a cap
on the media as long as we can.

05:14.792 --> 05:16.446
Means no one
but the techs and us

05:16.490 --> 05:18.405
step foot on this property.

05:19.928 --> 05:22.365
[indistinct chatter]

05:22.409 --> 05:25.412
[camera shutter snapping]

05:29.590 --> 05:31.113
- Hey.
- Hey.

05:31.156 --> 05:33.376
- It is absolute overkill
in here.

05:33.420 --> 05:34.725
Had to be personal.

05:36.031 --> 05:37.075
This is Claudia Ward.

05:37.119 --> 05:38.947
She's the matriarch
of the family.

05:38.990 --> 05:40.818
House is in her name.

05:40.862 --> 05:42.472
One GSW to the back
of the head.

05:42.516 --> 05:44.039
Looks like she was running
to the front door.

05:44.082 --> 05:46.607
Her kill is the cleanest
out of all of them.

05:46.650 --> 05:48.913
This is her son
Benny Ward, 22.

05:48.957 --> 05:50.959
He's got bruising,
defense wounds.

05:51.002 --> 05:53.004
Looks like
he was pistol-whipped.

05:53.048 --> 05:54.658
His sister's here
in the kitchen.

05:54.702 --> 06:01.709
<i>♪</i>

06:03.058 --> 06:05.974
Gabrielle Ward,
Makayla's mother.

06:06.017 --> 06:08.019
One GSW to the stomach,
two to the back.

06:08.063 --> 06:11.022
She...bled out slow.

06:11.066 --> 06:12.720
- No sign of robbery yet.

06:12.763 --> 06:14.983
Cash was left on the table
in the front.

06:15.026 --> 06:16.027
- Huh.

06:16.071 --> 06:17.899
- Purses and wallets
in plain view.

06:19.204 --> 06:20.945
- No forced entry?

06:20.989 --> 06:22.164
- No, doesn't look like it.

06:22.207 --> 06:24.471
Front and the back door
were unlocked.

06:25.776 --> 06:28.083
- It's the little girl?
- Yeah.

06:28.126 --> 06:30.868
Prints match Makayla's shoes.
We think she was inside.

06:30.912 --> 06:32.957
She was probably hiding,
maybe here in the pantry.

06:33.001 --> 06:35.090
Shooter makes his way
to the front.

06:35.133 --> 06:36.918
She finds her mom bleeding,

06:36.961 --> 06:39.137
takes off out the back.

06:39.181 --> 06:41.052
- Mom told her to run.

06:42.184 --> 06:44.229
- Yeah.

06:44.273 --> 06:46.841
<i>[solemn music]</i>

06:46.884 --> 06:49.757
<i>♪</i>

06:49.800 --> 06:51.976
- Med cleared the girl.
No injuries.

06:52.020 --> 06:54.544
- Yeah, Burgess is with her.
We're waiting on DCFS.

06:54.588 --> 06:56.633
- All right, talk to me.
What do we got?

06:56.677 --> 06:58.548
- Ward family,
no priors except for Benny,

06:58.592 --> 06:59.984
who has a year-old
possession charge.

07:00.028 --> 07:01.595
- Thinking the shooter
might've used a suppressor.

07:01.638 --> 07:03.901
No one heard or saw anything,
and zero cams.

07:03.945 --> 07:06.251
- I connected with Forensics.
It's gonna take them some time.

07:06.295 --> 07:07.905
Three bodies,
that's a lot of DNA.

07:07.949 --> 07:09.037
- Four people living
in one house,

07:09.080 --> 07:10.560
that's a lot of foot traffic.

07:10.604 --> 07:12.170
- Well, we work the why first.

07:12.214 --> 07:14.172
Home invasion gone wrong?
A hit?

07:14.216 --> 07:16.653
Family disagreement?
Murder turned triple homicide?

07:16.697 --> 07:18.481
There can be plenty
of possibilities,

07:18.525 --> 07:20.614
but it's gonna be the why
that gets us to who.

07:20.657 --> 07:22.529
- I got a possible why.

07:22.572 --> 07:24.008
Benny Ward's yearlong
possession charge

07:24.052 --> 07:25.227
is not the full story.

07:25.270 --> 07:26.881
Kid's got a couple
gang dispersal cards,

07:26.924 --> 07:28.622
quite the social media
presence.

07:28.665 --> 07:29.971
According to the Gang Unit
and CPIC,

07:30.014 --> 07:31.842
he's been the enforcer
for the Gangster Prophets

07:31.886 --> 07:33.104
for the past two years.

07:33.148 --> 07:34.105
- Okay, so he had enemies.

07:34.149 --> 07:35.193
- He's got a lot of enemies.

07:35.237 --> 07:36.760
CPIC sent over a whole list.

07:36.804 --> 07:38.283
Over a dozen death threats
online.

07:38.327 --> 07:39.763
- Hmm.
- So wait.

07:39.807 --> 07:41.112
We think this is
gang retribution?

07:41.156 --> 07:42.897
They'd do a whole family
like that?

07:42.940 --> 07:45.856
- Listen, no reason is ever
gonna feel like enough, Adam.

07:45.900 --> 07:47.945
- DCFS is downstairs.
- All right, so run it down.

07:47.989 --> 07:49.294
Talk to your CIs.

07:49.338 --> 07:51.819
If this was a gang hit,
the streets will know.

07:55.213 --> 07:58.042
- Sarge.
They're here.

07:58.086 --> 07:59.261
- Lieutenant, good to see you.

07:59.304 --> 08:01.132
- Hey, wanted
to work this one myself.

08:01.176 --> 08:03.526
- 30 years.
Juvenile cases.

08:03.570 --> 08:05.136
Happy to have you on this one.

08:05.180 --> 08:06.877
- This is Alanah Mercer
with DCFS.

08:06.921 --> 08:08.618
- Is someone from
Makayla's family on the way?

08:08.662 --> 08:11.621
- Unfortunately, most of the
girl's family was in that home.

08:11.665 --> 08:13.318
She doesn't have any father
on the birth certificate.

08:13.362 --> 08:16.278
Only immediate kin
is a cousin of Gabrielle's.

08:16.321 --> 08:18.062
We're trying to track her down.

08:18.106 --> 08:20.325
- I understand you believe
Makayla is a potential witness.

08:20.369 --> 08:22.806
- We have evidence
that she was in the home.

08:22.850 --> 08:24.982
As of now, she might be
our only witness.

08:25.026 --> 08:26.636
- She still hasn't said
a word, though.

08:26.680 --> 08:28.551
- At her age,
that's pretty expected.

08:28.595 --> 08:30.727
Trauma like that,
fear, it floods the system.

08:30.771 --> 08:32.163
Doesn't go away quick.

08:32.207 --> 08:34.688
Might be days, weeks, months
before she talks about it.

08:34.731 --> 08:36.820
- Well, we would like
to question her if possible.

08:36.864 --> 08:38.996
- You can try as long
as it's not harming her,

08:39.040 --> 08:41.129
but Alanah and the hospital
need to be kept apprised.

08:41.172 --> 08:42.565
- No problem.

08:42.609 --> 08:43.914
Kim, you run point.

08:43.958 --> 08:45.699
- Sarge, I don't have
any experience

08:45.742 --> 08:47.309
working with children.

08:47.352 --> 08:48.963
A youth detective would be--
- You were her first contact?

08:49.006 --> 08:50.181
- Yeah, I was
her first contact.

08:50.225 --> 08:51.792
- Priority
is to make her feel safe.

08:51.835 --> 08:54.098
She certainly won't talk
or move forward until then.

08:54.142 --> 08:55.317
Right now,
you're the best option

08:55.360 --> 08:57.232
to make her feel that way.

08:57.275 --> 08:58.712
- Okay.

09:05.632 --> 09:06.850
Hey.

09:06.894 --> 09:08.678
- She hasn't talked yet.

09:09.810 --> 09:11.855
- How am I supposed
to make this kid feel safe

09:11.899 --> 09:13.204
after what happened?

09:14.423 --> 09:16.599
- Honestly, I don't know.

09:16.643 --> 09:19.863
But I don't think
there's just one right way.

09:20.734 --> 09:22.736
- All right.
- Mm-hmm.

09:22.779 --> 09:24.955
<i>[soft music]</i>

09:24.999 --> 09:27.044
- I brought you
something to eat.

09:27.088 --> 09:34.095
<i>♪</i>

09:35.705 --> 09:37.098
So I--

09:37.141 --> 09:41.058
I was hoping and thinking

09:41.102 --> 09:43.234
we could maybe talk a little
about what happened

09:43.278 --> 09:45.236
before I found you
on the street.

09:45.280 --> 09:46.803
What do you think?

09:48.936 --> 09:50.720
Okay?

09:50.764 --> 09:53.114
Did you run there
from your house?

09:58.685 --> 10:01.035
Do you remember being at home?

10:04.342 --> 10:07.998
Makayla, do you remember
anything about what happened?

10:10.305 --> 10:11.959
Anything at all?

10:16.964 --> 10:18.748
Okay.

10:18.792 --> 10:25.799
<i>♪</i>

11:05.012 --> 11:07.275
- Hey.
- [groans]

11:07.318 --> 11:09.843
Nah, nah.
You told me we were done.

11:09.886 --> 11:11.192
You told me you was going
to New York.

11:11.235 --> 11:12.323
- I'm back now.

11:12.367 --> 11:13.411
- Nope.

11:13.455 --> 11:14.717
[inhales deeply, sighs]

11:14.761 --> 11:16.980
Look, I ain't stepping foot
near no massacre.

11:17.024 --> 11:18.199
- That's very perceptive
of you, Marv.

11:18.242 --> 11:19.287
I never told you
why we're here.

11:19.330 --> 11:20.767
- It's bad karma.

11:20.810 --> 11:22.333
You can't go pirouetting
around a whole family murdered.

11:22.377 --> 11:24.205
- Pirouetting?
- It's not good for the soul.

11:24.248 --> 11:26.337
- Hey.
- Nah.

11:26.381 --> 11:28.296
You can't bribe me on this one.
- No?

11:28.339 --> 11:29.732
'Cause your sister
called me last week

11:29.776 --> 11:31.081
saying you broke into her place
looking for cash.

11:31.125 --> 11:32.561
Scared the hell
out of your niece.

11:32.604 --> 11:34.215
- I didn't mean to do that.
- All we need is a name.

11:34.258 --> 11:35.999
Benny was a Gangster Prophet,
and we know the streets

11:36.043 --> 11:38.915
are talking, so who are they
saying killed his family?

11:38.959 --> 11:41.004
- Marv, when have I ever

11:41.048 --> 11:44.225
asked you a question
not worth answering for me?

11:44.268 --> 11:45.226
- The streets are saying

11:45.269 --> 11:46.836
a Southside Hustler
took them out.

11:46.880 --> 11:48.490
- Okay, you got a name?

11:48.533 --> 11:50.405
- Tru!

11:50.448 --> 11:52.146
Goes by Tru.
He killed them.

11:52.189 --> 11:53.538
- Why?

11:53.582 --> 11:55.976
- Benny and Tru got into it
a couple of weeks ago.

11:56.019 --> 11:57.499
Guys broke it up

11:57.542 --> 11:59.849
but not before Benny jacked
a beer bottle into Tru's eye.

12:01.068 --> 12:02.809
The killings were payback,

12:02.852 --> 12:04.114
karma.

12:04.158 --> 12:05.855
- This him?

12:05.899 --> 12:08.031
- Yeah, that's him.

12:08.075 --> 12:09.772
He usually hangs
at the Y courts.

12:09.816 --> 12:10.860
Plays ball there.

12:10.904 --> 12:12.209
- Call your sister
and apologize.

12:14.908 --> 12:17.780
Truman Powell, 27.
Got two priors for assault.

12:17.824 --> 12:21.828
CPIC has him on for multiple
threats against Benny online,

12:21.871 --> 12:24.308
and he's got an open warrant
for aggravated battery.

12:24.352 --> 12:25.396
- Works for me.

12:27.616 --> 12:29.792
I got the front door covered.
Let's take him outside.

12:29.836 --> 12:31.446
You got an anchor?
- Yeah.

12:31.489 --> 12:34.188
Got my eye on you.
Got your six.

12:34.231 --> 12:35.232
- He's coming out.

12:35.276 --> 12:38.235
<i>[tense music]</i>

12:38.279 --> 12:42.849
<i>♪</i>

12:42.892 --> 12:45.460
Truman Powell, Chicago PD!
Stop!

12:47.897 --> 12:49.377
- Truman, Chicago PD!

12:49.420 --> 12:51.771
[both grunting]

12:54.948 --> 12:57.167
Hey, hey, hey!
Arm up! Arm up!

12:57.211 --> 12:58.908
- Okay, we're done!
Stop fighting!

12:58.952 --> 13:01.345
Turn over.

13:01.389 --> 13:03.347
Don't move.

13:03.391 --> 13:05.436
- [grunts]

13:05.480 --> 13:06.873
- All right, let's go.

13:06.916 --> 13:09.049
Get up!
- [groans]

13:09.092 --> 13:13.314
<i>♪</i>

13:16.534 --> 13:18.101
- You got
an outstanding warrant,

13:18.145 --> 13:19.233
history of violence,

13:19.276 --> 13:21.148
multiple threats
against a dead man,

13:21.191 --> 13:22.627
and we ran your car, Tru;
you're four blocks

13:22.671 --> 13:25.848
from the Wards' house
two hours before the killings.

13:25.892 --> 13:28.416
- What, you just wanna
sit there and smile at me?

13:28.459 --> 13:30.200
- Hey, if I were you,

13:30.244 --> 13:32.333
I'd at least give us
the bare minimum.

13:33.595 --> 13:35.902
You got an alibi
you wanna give us?

13:35.945 --> 13:38.469
- I got a lawyer.
I'll call him now.

13:40.602 --> 13:42.647
- You catch that?
- Yeah, he knows something.

13:42.691 --> 13:45.128
He's good at pretending
he's not scared, though.

13:45.172 --> 13:47.217
- Hey, Upton.

13:47.261 --> 13:48.653
Not just calling me anymore.

13:48.697 --> 13:51.134
Now the feds are
sending me packages for you.

13:51.178 --> 13:52.919
- Thank you.
- You're gonna have

13:52.962 --> 13:54.137
to rein this in at some point,

13:54.181 --> 13:56.009
not that I don't like
being your mail lady.

13:56.052 --> 13:58.185
- I know. Thank you.
- Uh-huh.

13:59.447 --> 14:01.928
- The feds?

14:01.971 --> 14:04.147
- Look, I don't care
if Tru's not talking.

14:04.191 --> 14:05.496
He's still looking good for it.

14:05.540 --> 14:07.150
- And ballistics came back.

14:07.194 --> 14:09.631
The bullets match an unsolved
Southside Hustler shoot.

14:09.674 --> 14:10.980
- Huh.
- Would make sense

14:11.024 --> 14:12.503
if it was a gang
pass-down piece.

14:12.547 --> 14:14.375
- All right,
so we hold Tru for 48,

14:14.418 --> 14:16.377
see if we can place him
at the scene.

14:16.420 --> 14:18.292
Hey, Kim make any progress
with the kid?

14:18.335 --> 14:19.815
- Not yet.

14:19.859 --> 14:21.382
Family Services are gonna have
to relocate her tonight.

14:21.425 --> 14:23.340
Kim's out trying something
right now.

14:23.384 --> 14:24.646
- All right, let's hit it.

14:27.954 --> 14:29.477
- What did the feds want?

14:32.001 --> 14:34.003
- It's a job offer.

14:34.047 --> 14:35.918
- Well, that's good.
Where at?

14:35.962 --> 14:37.659
- New York?

14:39.966 --> 14:41.489
- Cool.

14:42.969 --> 14:45.928
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:45.972 --> 14:52.979
<i>♪</i>

15:33.193 --> 15:34.977
- Stayed in the same place?
- Yeah.

15:35.021 --> 15:36.979
- Okay, great.

15:37.023 --> 15:38.285
Hey.

15:40.069 --> 15:42.071
I went and I grabbed

15:42.115 --> 15:44.334
what I hoped
were favorites.

15:44.378 --> 15:47.337
Got this guy.
Seemed nice.

15:51.211 --> 15:53.430
How about--oh.

15:53.474 --> 15:55.476
Penguin, huh?

15:59.784 --> 16:02.570
[sighs]

16:02.613 --> 16:05.094
Um...

16:05.138 --> 16:07.009
and I brought
your mom's sweater.

16:07.053 --> 16:09.229
Thought maybe you
might wanna wear it.

16:09.272 --> 16:12.232
<i>[somber music]</i>

16:12.275 --> 16:16.758
<i>♪</i>

16:16.801 --> 16:18.673
Let's put it on you.

16:19.717 --> 16:22.590
'Cause I have some friends
I want you to meet.

16:22.633 --> 16:24.766
This is my friend Alanah,

16:24.809 --> 16:27.116
the lady you met before.

16:27.160 --> 16:29.205
This is Trudy.
You know her.

16:29.249 --> 16:30.380
And that's Claire.

16:30.424 --> 16:31.642
Claire has
this really nice house

16:31.686 --> 16:33.035
she's gonna take you to.

16:33.079 --> 16:34.123
You're gonna go, you're gonna
get a good nice rest,

16:34.167 --> 16:35.777
and then you're gonna
come here,

16:35.820 --> 16:38.475
and then you and I are gonna
talk in the morning, all right?

16:38.519 --> 16:40.390
- Ready to go, kiddo?

16:42.827 --> 16:44.829
- Do you want me
to come with you?

16:44.873 --> 16:50.357
<i>♪</i>

16:50.400 --> 16:52.576
Okay.

16:52.620 --> 16:55.318
All right,
we'll grab your things.

16:55.362 --> 16:57.146
- Bedroom's just down the hall
to your right.

16:57.190 --> 16:58.321
- Okay.
You're going the right way.

16:58.365 --> 17:00.367
It's this door right here,
all right?

17:03.761 --> 17:07.330
Wow, look at the stars.
Those are cool.

17:07.374 --> 17:14.207
<i>♪</i>

17:15.208 --> 17:17.645
I brought you something,

17:17.688 --> 17:19.212
your pajamas.

17:19.255 --> 17:26.219
<i>♪</i>

17:28.743 --> 17:31.137
You know what I used to do
when I was younger?

17:31.180 --> 17:36.142
I would line all my stuffies
at the end of my bed

17:36.185 --> 17:39.319
so it was like this little army
keeping me safe.

17:42.235 --> 17:44.802
Oh, yeah.

17:44.846 --> 17:46.717
Kind of dumb.

17:48.284 --> 17:50.591
[sighs]

17:52.375 --> 17:54.247
It's okay if you're scared,
Makayla.

17:54.290 --> 17:55.813
I've been scared before.

17:55.857 --> 17:57.859
I know the feeling pretty well.

17:57.902 --> 18:03.125
<i>♪</i>

18:03.169 --> 18:06.259
Oh, yeah.
Adults get scared for sure.

18:08.783 --> 18:10.176
There was a time
a few months ago.

18:10.219 --> 18:13.788
I was doing my job,
and somebody tried to hurt me.

18:13.831 --> 18:17.183
And I was so scared, but...

18:17.226 --> 18:19.228
that's the good thing
about being scared.

18:19.272 --> 18:21.143
Sometimes it's like
this reminder

18:21.187 --> 18:23.754
that you have to be brave,
you have to fight.

18:23.798 --> 18:25.147
So I fought.

18:28.759 --> 18:31.284
- But I ran.

18:34.765 --> 18:36.941
- That's okay.

18:36.985 --> 18:39.161
Running is a kind of fighting.

18:39.205 --> 18:42.599
- I ran outside.

18:42.643 --> 18:45.472
But she came looking.

18:45.515 --> 18:48.170
- She?
You saw a woman in your house?

18:50.259 --> 18:53.132
What was her name?
You know her?

18:54.916 --> 18:56.439
Okay.

18:56.483 --> 18:59.616
- But she was looking for me.

18:59.660 --> 19:01.792
She was calling my name.

19:01.836 --> 19:04.752
But I hid outside.

19:04.795 --> 19:06.145
- Okay.

19:09.017 --> 19:11.715
- Can I go to sleep now?

19:13.848 --> 19:16.633
- Yeah, Makayla.
You can go to bed.

19:16.677 --> 19:19.593
I will be right back,
and I will...

19:19.636 --> 19:20.811
tuck you in, okay?

19:20.855 --> 19:21.899
Give me two minutes.

19:21.943 --> 19:27.688
<i>♪</i>

19:27.731 --> 19:29.255
Claire?
What's wrong?

19:29.298 --> 19:31.474
- I just--I thought
I saw someone.

19:31.518 --> 19:33.824
It's probably a shadow.
- What exactly did you see?

19:33.868 --> 19:35.304
- Someone along
the side of the house,

19:35.348 --> 19:37.654
like they were trying
not to be seen.

19:37.698 --> 19:39.221
[gasps]
[glass shatters]

19:39.265 --> 19:40.222
- Get down!
[Makayla screams]

19:40.266 --> 19:41.571
- What's going on?
- Just get down!

19:41.615 --> 19:42.703
Makayla?

19:42.746 --> 19:46.446
<i>[tense music]</i>

19:46.489 --> 19:48.361
Makayla!

19:48.404 --> 19:49.579
- I'm here.

19:49.623 --> 19:50.798
- Get behind me.
Get behind me!

19:50.841 --> 19:52.365
Grab my hand, okay?

19:52.408 --> 19:54.367
You're okay.
You're all right.

19:54.410 --> 19:56.847
Stay behind me no matter what.
No matter what.

19:56.891 --> 19:58.414
Claire, get down low.

19:58.458 --> 20:00.242
Get low and come to me.
Come to me!

20:00.286 --> 20:01.504
Come to me quick.
Take my phone.

20:01.548 --> 20:02.853
Call 911.
Get in the bathtub.

20:02.897 --> 20:04.333
Leave the line open.
Take Makayla.

20:04.377 --> 20:06.292
- Come here, sweetie.
- You're okay, Makayla!

20:06.335 --> 20:08.294
You're okay.
You're okay.

20:08.337 --> 20:09.512
- Two intruders in the house.

20:09.556 --> 20:12.559
I'm with Officer Kim Burgess...

20:12.602 --> 20:14.213
[door clatters]
[Makayla screams]

20:16.867 --> 20:18.565
[gunshots]

20:18.608 --> 20:25.615
<i>♪</i>

20:29.706 --> 20:31.708
- So patrol arrived
after three minutes,

20:31.752 --> 20:32.796
spotted an SUV
fleeing the scene:

20:32.840 --> 20:34.624
black Nissan Pathfinder,
no plates.

20:34.668 --> 20:36.017
- They lost the vehicle?
- Yeah.

20:36.060 --> 20:37.888
They followed it all the way
to Wacker for a mile,

20:37.932 --> 20:39.281
and then they lost it.
- You okay?

20:39.325 --> 20:40.848
- Yeah, I saw
two different offenders,

20:40.891 --> 20:42.502
both masked and gloved up.

20:42.545 --> 20:44.982
I wasn't able
to discern race, height.

20:45.026 --> 20:47.594
Things happened very fast,
but they were here for Makayla.

20:47.637 --> 20:49.160
- What makes you think that?

20:49.204 --> 20:51.119
- They crashed this location
ten minutes after we arrived.

20:51.162 --> 20:53.817
They hit her window first.
They must've followed us here.

20:53.861 --> 20:55.645
- Opens more questions
than answers.

20:55.689 --> 20:58.300
- You think it was a hit?
- I don't know what it was.

20:58.344 --> 21:00.171
But Makayla had finally
started talking.

21:00.215 --> 21:01.825
She said she saw a woman
in her house

21:01.869 --> 21:03.044
at the time of the murders

21:03.087 --> 21:05.176
and the woman was
calling out her name.

21:05.220 --> 21:07.657
- Okay, either way, we do need
to protect the child

21:07.701 --> 21:09.180
until we have answers.
- Yeah.

21:09.224 --> 21:11.052
- I'll call WITSEC
and get her into protection.

21:11.095 --> 21:13.010
- Mm.
- She's staying with me.

21:13.054 --> 21:14.882
- No, she can't.
That's not protocol.

21:14.925 --> 21:16.449
- Well, let's go
against protocol.

21:16.492 --> 21:19.278
- Right now, your job is--
- My job is to protect the kid.

21:19.321 --> 21:22.106
- Is she always like this?
- Yeah, she always is.

21:22.150 --> 21:24.848
- Well, she's not wrong,
and if it was about Makayla,

21:24.892 --> 21:26.894
it's probably best
we keep it in-house.

21:26.937 --> 21:28.548
Someone ID'd her location.

21:28.591 --> 21:29.940
- Lieutenant,
with all due respect,

21:29.984 --> 21:31.464
you can play it
by protocol or not.

21:31.507 --> 21:33.117
You can take me off the case.
You can detail me to WITSEC.

21:33.161 --> 21:34.989
I don't care how it happens,

21:35.032 --> 21:36.904
but that kid stays with me.

21:38.079 --> 21:40.560
- Okay, we'll get
a safe house approved.

21:40.603 --> 21:42.170
- Thank you.

21:42.213 --> 21:43.345
- You gotta have
the teddy bear.

21:43.389 --> 21:45.304
That's a classic, right?

21:45.347 --> 21:47.915
And one more.
Which guy here?

21:47.958 --> 21:49.873
You point.

21:49.917 --> 21:51.875
This guy?
This is your favorite?

21:51.919 --> 21:53.050
Okay.

21:53.094 --> 21:55.357
What am I looking at here?

21:55.401 --> 21:57.185
What is this?
- Platypus?

21:57.228 --> 21:58.795
- A platypus.

21:58.839 --> 22:02.233
How could I forget
the shiny-tailed platypus?

22:02.277 --> 22:04.235
Right here.
Is he your favorite?

22:04.279 --> 22:05.802
Yeah, he stays with you, then.

22:05.846 --> 22:07.848
- Okay, it's bedtime.
Let's go.

22:07.891 --> 22:10.851
<i>[soft music]</i>

22:10.894 --> 22:11.852
<i>♪</i>

22:11.895 --> 22:13.288
You want us to stay with you?

22:15.899 --> 22:17.640
Okay?

22:17.684 --> 22:19.947
Okay. Go on.

22:22.689 --> 22:23.690
All right.

22:25.953 --> 22:28.782
Scooch down.

22:28.825 --> 22:30.914
There you go.

22:34.962 --> 22:36.355
- Good night, Makayla.

22:39.793 --> 22:41.055
[sighs]

22:45.233 --> 22:46.669
- As we've repeatedly said,

22:46.713 --> 22:48.671
my client won't be answering
any more questions.

22:48.715 --> 22:51.065
- And as I have said,
I'm not asking any questions.

22:51.108 --> 22:52.458
I'm just giving him the info.

22:52.501 --> 22:54.764
We learned that there was
a woman inside that house,

22:54.808 --> 22:56.113
so clearly,
we're missing something.

22:56.157 --> 22:57.898
- He's got nothing to say.
- Look, Truman,

22:57.941 --> 23:00.117
you're gonna get booked on your
warrant at the end of the day,

23:00.161 --> 23:01.945
so we don't have to release you
in 48.

23:01.989 --> 23:03.120
We can keep pressing
till we make this fit.

23:03.164 --> 23:04.121
- All right, this is enough.

23:04.165 --> 23:06.080
- You got motive, no alibi.

23:06.123 --> 23:07.516
You're in the area.

23:07.560 --> 23:08.952
You see how easy I can make it
that you and your girl,

23:08.996 --> 23:10.084
you go for a little joyride,

23:10.127 --> 23:11.520
you're looking
to settle some scores,

23:11.564 --> 23:13.783
you entered the house and
slaughtered everyone inside?

23:13.827 --> 23:15.176
- I'd never stepped foot
in that house.

23:15.219 --> 23:17.918
- You would never step foot
in that house?

23:17.961 --> 23:20.050
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:20.094 --> 23:21.878
Why'd you say it like that,

23:21.922 --> 23:23.663
you would never?

23:23.706 --> 23:28.450
<i>♪</i>

23:28.494 --> 23:30.452
[vehicle backfires]
- [gasps] Oh, no.

23:30.496 --> 23:31.845
- No.
Hey, hey, hey.

23:31.888 --> 23:34.456
It was just, um--
it was just a truck, okay?

23:34.500 --> 23:37.416
- But what if they come back
tonight?

23:37.459 --> 23:39.330
- What if who
comes back tonight?

23:39.374 --> 23:46.337
<i>♪</i>

23:46.381 --> 23:49.210
- This little girl...

23:49.253 --> 23:52.779
watched her mother
get killed in front of her.

23:52.822 --> 23:54.868
Her whole family...

23:54.911 --> 23:57.218
was murdered in front of her.

23:57.261 --> 23:59.263
This tiny kid

23:59.307 --> 24:01.178
has to deal with those moments
of violence

24:01.222 --> 24:03.920
for the rest of her life.

24:05.052 --> 24:06.401
Look at me.

24:08.403 --> 24:11.406
You said you would never
step foot in that house,

24:11.450 --> 24:13.843
and I'm guessing
that's because of retribution,

24:13.887 --> 24:14.931
because of Benny.

24:14.975 --> 24:15.932
- It's not because of Benny.

24:15.976 --> 24:17.151
- Truman, I am advising you--

24:17.194 --> 24:19.022
- I would never step foot
in that house

24:19.066 --> 24:21.808
because of her.

24:21.851 --> 24:24.419
She's the reason why.
She's protected.

24:24.463 --> 24:27.074
I go near her, I end up dead.

24:30.251 --> 24:32.514
- When you say "they,"
who are you talking about, huh?

24:32.558 --> 24:35.212
- Mm, my daddy and her.

24:35.256 --> 24:37.519
- Your daddy?

24:37.563 --> 24:39.260
At your house?

24:41.567 --> 24:45.092
- The woman said he was there.

24:45.135 --> 24:48.051
She told me to come out,

24:48.095 --> 24:51.272
that my daddy was there
to take me home.

24:51.315 --> 24:58.105
<i>♪</i>

24:58.148 --> 25:01.369
- All right.
This is Tariq Morris.

25:01.412 --> 25:03.458
He is a notorious
Southside Hustler.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.504
He's extremely violent.
He's got 12 priors.

25:05.547 --> 25:06.853
He's feared by his faction.

25:06.896 --> 25:08.376
According to Truman,

25:08.419 --> 25:11.031
Tariq is Makayla's father.

25:11.074 --> 25:13.424
- So Tariq and Gabrielle

25:13.468 --> 25:15.905
dated briefly years ago.

25:15.949 --> 25:17.516
Gabrielle got pregnant.

25:17.559 --> 25:20.040
Tariq ended up in Stateville
on a six-year prison sentence.

25:20.083 --> 25:21.084
Before the baby was born,

25:21.128 --> 25:22.433
Gabrielle broke it off
with him.

25:22.477 --> 25:25.132
- And Tariq just got released?
- Three days ago.

25:25.175 --> 25:27.090
- Makayla said there was
a woman in the house

25:27.134 --> 25:28.309
calling out her name,

25:28.352 --> 25:30.093
saying her father was there
to pick her up.

25:30.137 --> 25:31.573
- They were looking
for the girl.

25:31.617 --> 25:33.923
- So it's been about Makayla
this whole time.

25:33.967 --> 25:35.446
They were there to kidnap her.

25:35.490 --> 25:38.014
<i>♪</i>

25:42.366 --> 25:44.194
- Okay.
- Hey.

25:44.238 --> 25:46.327
Stateville sent over
visitor logs for Tariq,

25:46.370 --> 25:47.720
so we firmed up a theory.

25:47.763 --> 25:49.417
Gabrielle went
to visit him once

25:49.460 --> 25:50.679
at the beginning
of his sentence.

25:50.723 --> 25:52.420
Didn't bring Makayla,
and she never went back.

25:52.463 --> 25:53.769
- I talked to a few guards,
Sarge.

25:53.813 --> 25:55.336
Apparently, that was
the exact visit

25:55.379 --> 25:56.598
that Gabrielle
broke up with him.

25:56.642 --> 25:58.295
Took the chance to get her
and her daughter

25:58.339 --> 25:59.645
the hell away from him.

25:59.688 --> 26:01.168
Stopped answering his messages
and his letters,

26:01.211 --> 26:02.604
just completely shut him out.

26:02.648 --> 26:05.085
- And he spent six years
in prison ruminating on it.

26:05.128 --> 26:06.390
- Right, so he goes
to that house.

26:06.434 --> 26:08.175
The entire family tries
to protect Makayla,

26:08.218 --> 26:09.393
and they get killed for it.

26:09.437 --> 26:11.134
- Think we've ID'd
our female accomplice:

26:11.178 --> 26:13.006
Nia Benson.

26:13.049 --> 26:15.269
Girl from the neighborhood,
half a dozen arrest priors,

26:15.312 --> 26:16.618
not a single charge on her.

26:16.662 --> 26:18.577
Started visiting Tariq
in prison about a year ago.

26:18.620 --> 26:20.143
- There's phone calls.
There's emails.

26:20.187 --> 26:21.623
There's hundreds of visits
between the two of them.

26:21.667 --> 26:23.625
This is a full-on
prison romance.

26:23.669 --> 26:25.235
- She also has
a black Nissan Pathfinder,

26:25.279 --> 26:27.411
which is the same SUV that
we found at the foster home.

26:27.455 --> 26:29.065
Ruzek's running her LKAs
right now.

26:29.109 --> 26:31.024
- Yo, I think I got her.

26:31.067 --> 26:33.069
Patrol just responded
to our BOLO

26:33.113 --> 26:34.114
at Nia's sister's house.

26:34.157 --> 26:35.550
There's a black
Nissan Pathfinder

26:35.594 --> 26:36.638
parked in the back alley.

26:36.682 --> 26:38.553
- Go grab her.

26:41.382 --> 26:42.339
[knocking]

26:42.383 --> 26:44.167
<i>- Hey. Please!</i>

26:44.211 --> 26:46.517
<i>Can somebody tell me
what's going on?</i>

26:46.561 --> 26:48.171
This guy won't
tell me anything.

26:48.215 --> 26:49.738
I don't even get
why I'm in here!

26:49.782 --> 26:51.131
Yo!

26:51.174 --> 26:52.698
- All right,
let me clue you in.

26:55.439 --> 26:57.659
We found your SUV at the scene

26:57.703 --> 26:59.705
of an attempted kidnapping.

26:59.748 --> 27:04.187
You match our descriptors
for a triple homicide.

27:04.231 --> 27:06.276
Your sister admitted to us

27:06.320 --> 27:08.496
that you asked her
for cash and a car.

27:08.539 --> 27:11.238
Said you wanted to skip town.

27:11.281 --> 27:13.109
Should I keep going?

27:13.153 --> 27:14.807
'Cause we searched
your sister's complex,

27:14.850 --> 27:17.505
found no trace of Tariq.

27:17.548 --> 27:18.854
So why don't we start there,

27:18.898 --> 27:20.377
only this time

27:20.421 --> 27:22.684
without the cute?

27:22.728 --> 27:25.252
Where is he?

27:25.295 --> 27:26.688
- I don't know.

27:26.732 --> 27:28.603
- Mm-hmm.

27:28.647 --> 27:32.172
- I-I-I-I don't know, okay?

27:32.215 --> 27:35.654
Look, it's not what you think.
- Okay.

27:35.697 --> 27:38.700
- Tariq was going crazy.
He put a gun to my head!

27:38.744 --> 27:40.702
He told me he would kill me
if I didn't drive him.

27:40.746 --> 27:42.356
I never left the car.

27:42.399 --> 27:43.618
- That sounds terrible,

27:43.662 --> 27:45.576
but see,
the only problem is,

27:45.620 --> 27:47.578
I read your record.

27:47.622 --> 27:50.146
Nia, I know you've been
in rooms like this before,

27:50.190 --> 27:52.409
and yet you never
been charged.

27:52.453 --> 27:54.760
So this routine,
it usually works for you, huh?

27:54.803 --> 27:56.544
- Four times
a person of interest,

27:56.587 --> 27:58.677
three arrests, zero charges.

27:58.720 --> 28:00.243
You know, the saying goes,

28:00.287 --> 28:01.462
you only get lucky
so many times

28:01.505 --> 28:04.204
before cops start thinking
you're smart.

28:04.247 --> 28:06.467
- Where's Tariq?
- I have no idea.

28:06.510 --> 28:08.295
- You were supposed
to pick him up.

28:08.338 --> 28:10.471
- No, I got away from him.

28:10.514 --> 28:13.343
- See, we got your phone.
You understand that?

28:13.387 --> 28:16.825
I read your texts.
I know your plan.

28:16.869 --> 28:19.741
- No, no.
I was lying to him.

28:19.785 --> 28:21.700
I never even knew
what he was up to, I swear--

28:21.743 --> 28:23.919
- I think you two wanted
a whole new life

28:23.963 --> 28:26.269
on the outside,
a perfect family.

28:26.313 --> 28:28.271
Only thing missing:

28:28.315 --> 28:30.796
a baby.

28:30.839 --> 28:33.276
So you two walked
into his ex-girlfriend's house

28:33.320 --> 28:34.887
to steal a child.

28:34.930 --> 28:38.673
And when her family tried
to defend her,

28:38.717 --> 28:40.588
you murdered every one of them.

28:42.764 --> 28:44.810
- I'm sorry.

28:44.853 --> 28:47.769
I don't know anything, okay?
- Hmm.

28:47.813 --> 28:49.684
- Tariq thought
his ex-girlfriend was a bitch,

28:49.728 --> 28:51.425
but the rest is news to me.

28:52.687 --> 28:54.384
I never left the car.

28:54.428 --> 28:57.213
I don't know where he is.

28:57.257 --> 29:00.216
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:00.260 --> 29:01.304
<i>♪</i>

29:01.348 --> 29:03.742
- Any progress on Tariq?
- Zero.

29:03.785 --> 29:05.613
Transit teams, state police
have been alerted,

29:05.656 --> 29:06.788
but so far, nothing.

29:06.832 --> 29:08.747
- Guy's hiding out,
waiting for his gal.

29:08.790 --> 29:10.792
- What about a lure?
We got her cell.

29:10.836 --> 29:12.489
We could do a bait and switch.
- I don't know.

29:12.533 --> 29:14.317
I mean, the texts on her phone
made it sound like

29:14.361 --> 29:15.971
she already knew where she
was picking Tariq up.

29:16.015 --> 29:17.364
If we change locations now,

29:17.407 --> 29:19.932
chances are,
he's gonna know it's us.

29:19.975 --> 29:23.674
- Look, it's simple.
We need Nia to talk.

29:23.718 --> 29:25.676
We're gonna have to use Makayla
as leverage.

29:25.720 --> 29:27.330
I mean, she was at the house.

29:27.374 --> 29:30.681
She can ID her
as an active participant.

29:30.725 --> 29:33.684
But I want no legal loopholes.

29:33.728 --> 29:35.730
We jump straight to a lineup,

29:35.774 --> 29:37.819
put Makayla in front of it.

29:37.863 --> 29:39.821
All right, let Burgess know.
- Mm.

29:39.865 --> 29:41.736
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

29:41.780 --> 29:43.956
- Okay, you're gonna look
at a line of people,

29:43.999 --> 29:45.696
and then you're just
gonna point to the lady

29:45.740 --> 29:47.002
that you saw at your house.

29:47.046 --> 29:48.830
They cannot see you,

29:48.874 --> 29:51.615
and it is gonna go really fast.

29:51.659 --> 29:54.488
Is that okay?

29:54.531 --> 29:55.706
Yeah.

29:55.750 --> 29:57.578
Okay.

29:57.621 --> 29:59.275
- If we're waiting all day,

29:59.319 --> 30:00.624
can I at least get a water
or something?

30:00.668 --> 30:01.974
- [whimpers]
- No, no, no, no, no.

30:02.017 --> 30:03.366
Hey, hey, look at me.

30:03.410 --> 30:04.454
You're okay.
Shut the door.

30:04.498 --> 30:05.978
Hey, take a deep breath.
Come here.

30:06.021 --> 30:07.588
I'm right here.
I'm not going anywhere.

30:07.631 --> 30:08.850
I'm not going anywhere!
Come here, come here.

30:08.894 --> 30:10.373
We're not going in there.

30:10.417 --> 30:12.593
<i>♪</i>

30:16.205 --> 30:17.859
- She was doing okay.

30:17.903 --> 30:18.947
We'll just go check on her
in a little bit.

30:18.991 --> 30:20.079
Kid's all right.

30:20.122 --> 30:22.429
She's with Platt
and a paramedic now.

30:22.472 --> 30:24.866
- Okay, give her a few hours.
Try again.

30:24.910 --> 30:26.476
- Or we resort
to a photo lineup.

30:26.520 --> 30:28.000
- No, I'm not putting her
through that.

30:28.043 --> 30:29.479
I'm not putting her
through any of that.

30:29.523 --> 30:31.394
If there's a chance
it's not good for her,

30:31.438 --> 30:33.092
we don't do it.

30:33.135 --> 30:34.702
- Okay, so what's the play?

30:34.745 --> 30:36.269
'Cause we got zero leads
on Tariq.

30:36.312 --> 30:38.706
Barely got a murder case
on Nia, and she knows it.

30:38.749 --> 30:41.187
- Nia doesn't know if Makayla's
behind the glass or not.

30:41.230 --> 30:42.362
- So you wanna do
a lineup anyway.

30:42.405 --> 30:44.146
- Yeah, I'll lie my ass off.

30:49.238 --> 30:51.110
- Okay.

30:51.153 --> 30:52.894
Just...

30:52.938 --> 30:54.765
make it as airtight as you can.

30:59.509 --> 31:02.338
- The witness ID'd you
from the lineup.

31:02.382 --> 31:03.992
They saw you enter
the Ward home,

31:04.036 --> 31:06.342
exit the Ward home,
and proceed into the backyard,

31:06.386 --> 31:08.257
where you were heard
calling a young girl's name:

31:08.301 --> 31:10.956
Makayla.

31:10.999 --> 31:12.435
From the DNA
they swabbed from you,

31:12.479 --> 31:14.916
they matched half a dozen
samples inside the Ward home,

31:14.960 --> 31:17.353
including on the body
of one of the victims.

31:18.920 --> 31:20.313
They are still
running your SUV,

31:20.356 --> 31:22.358
but they were able to confirm
two traces of blood

31:22.402 --> 31:23.882
not visible to the naked eye:

31:23.925 --> 31:24.926
one on the driver's mat

31:24.970 --> 31:26.362
and the other
on the passenger seat.

31:26.406 --> 31:28.321
This is quite a lot
of evidence, Nia,

31:28.364 --> 31:29.757
more than we hoped for,

31:29.800 --> 31:32.368
so it won't matter
if you shot anyone yourself.

31:32.412 --> 31:33.892
You were there.
You participated.

31:33.935 --> 31:35.763
You will be charged
one count of home invasion,

31:35.806 --> 31:37.460
two counts attempted
aggravated kidnapping,

31:37.504 --> 31:40.202
and three counts of murder.

31:40.246 --> 31:41.812
So this right here, you and me,

31:41.856 --> 31:44.032
it's gonna be your only chance
to help yourself.

31:44.076 --> 31:47.209
I need you to tell me
where Tariq is.

31:47.253 --> 31:49.516
- [chuckles]

31:49.559 --> 31:51.170
- Six counts, Nia.

31:51.213 --> 31:53.563
These are charges
you do not walk back.

31:53.607 --> 31:55.043
Where is he?

31:55.087 --> 31:57.350
- Bitch, I don't believe you.

31:57.393 --> 31:58.960
<i>- You don't believe what?</i>

31:59.004 --> 32:01.876
- She's gonna keep going.

32:01.920 --> 32:04.270
- That this
is your last chance?

32:04.313 --> 32:05.706
You understand, right?

32:05.749 --> 32:08.056
I walk out that door,
the ball rolls on from here.

32:08.100 --> 32:09.362
You understand that?

32:09.405 --> 32:11.930
- Guess I should call
my lawyer, then, huh?

32:11.973 --> 32:14.280
- Yeah, sure.

32:14.323 --> 32:16.151
Call your lawyer.

32:16.195 --> 32:18.414
See, the truth is, Nia,

32:18.458 --> 32:21.417
I don't need your cooperation.

32:21.461 --> 32:23.942
I came in here
'cause I was obligated to.

32:25.334 --> 32:26.596
And I sure as hell was hoping

32:26.640 --> 32:29.164
I wouldn't have to give you
a damn thing...

32:29.208 --> 32:30.209
bitch.

32:32.341 --> 32:33.821
Hey, Fernandez?

32:33.864 --> 32:35.344
Patrol officer
will be here soon.

32:35.388 --> 32:37.259
He'll take you to booking.
You can call your lawyer there.

32:37.303 --> 32:38.869
I'm guessing you'll be
transferred out of state

32:38.913 --> 32:40.219
in the morning.
- Out of state?

32:40.262 --> 32:42.917
- Mm, Indiana.

32:45.006 --> 32:48.270
Claudia Ward, the grandmother,
she was a postal worker.

32:48.314 --> 32:50.229
- Is that true?
- No.

32:50.272 --> 32:51.839
<i>- What the hell
does that matter?</i>

32:51.882 --> 32:52.971
- She's a federal employee.

32:53.014 --> 32:54.015
You kill a federal employee,

32:54.059 --> 32:55.451
the government
picks up the case.

32:55.495 --> 32:56.626
Federal charges.

32:56.670 --> 32:58.193
You'll be transferred
to Terre Haute.

32:58.237 --> 33:00.500
- Whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa.

33:00.543 --> 33:03.024
I know Terre Haute.

33:03.068 --> 33:05.026
Don't they have death row
at Terre Haute?

33:05.070 --> 33:06.375
- They do.

33:06.419 --> 33:07.463
I told you the charges, Nia.

33:07.507 --> 33:09.422
Where'd you think
you were going?

33:09.465 --> 33:10.466
- No, no.

33:10.510 --> 33:17.473
<i>♪</i>

33:17.517 --> 33:20.085
- Nice play.

33:20.128 --> 33:22.565
<i>- Fine!</i>

33:22.609 --> 33:24.393
<i>I'll tell you,</i>

33:24.437 --> 33:26.395
<i>but you gotta say I helped.</i>

33:26.439 --> 33:29.398
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

33:29.442 --> 33:36.449
<i>♪</i>

33:46.589 --> 33:49.114
- Upton, you good?

33:49.157 --> 33:50.898
- Parked and ready.

33:53.074 --> 33:55.511
- All right, heads up,
Tariq is coming out.

33:55.555 --> 34:02.562
<i>♪</i>

34:12.702 --> 34:15.314
[cell phone buzzes]

34:15.357 --> 34:16.445
- Nia, you here?

34:20.232 --> 34:21.407
- Gun.
- That you?

34:21.450 --> 34:22.669
- Move in now.

34:24.366 --> 34:27.630
- Chicago PD!
Put your hands up!

34:27.674 --> 34:29.415
Put your hands up, Tariq.

34:29.458 --> 34:30.459
Look around, man.

34:30.503 --> 34:32.070
You got six guns
trained on you.

34:32.113 --> 34:34.072
It's over.

34:34.115 --> 34:35.334
Put your hands up.

34:35.377 --> 34:40.208
<i>♪</i>

34:40.252 --> 34:41.514
- She was my baby.

34:41.557 --> 34:44.082
- She's still your baby.
- I just wanted my baby!

34:45.126 --> 34:46.301
They took her from me, man!

34:46.345 --> 34:47.389
- Tariq, you listen to me.

34:47.433 --> 34:48.651
You calm down, all right?

34:50.566 --> 34:52.655
You raise that gun even
a little, you will be shot,

34:52.699 --> 34:53.700
and not once.

34:53.743 --> 34:55.093
Every cop here is gonna shoot,

34:55.136 --> 34:56.398
and that is six bullets.

34:56.442 --> 34:57.878
After everything you did,

34:57.921 --> 34:59.401
I don't think that's how
you want this thing to end:

34:59.445 --> 35:00.576
bleeding out in the dirt,

35:00.620 --> 35:03.144
never seeing
your baby girl again.

35:03.188 --> 35:04.319
Tariq, you listen to me.

35:04.363 --> 35:05.973
You toss that gun,
you still have a chance

35:06.016 --> 35:07.409
'cause you still got a kid,

35:07.453 --> 35:09.063
that kid's still got a father,

35:09.107 --> 35:10.238
and you are still alive.

35:10.282 --> 35:11.413
Toss that gun.

35:11.457 --> 35:13.111
- [groans]

35:13.154 --> 35:15.461
- You toss that gun, Tariq!

35:18.333 --> 35:20.596
- On your knees!

35:20.640 --> 35:22.120
Drop the phone!

35:22.163 --> 35:29.127
<i>♪</i>

35:32.521 --> 35:34.610
- I'm never gonna
see her again, am I?

35:34.654 --> 35:36.438
- I sure as hell hope not.

35:36.482 --> 35:39.441
<i>[solemn music]</i>

35:39.485 --> 35:43.706
<i>♪</i>

35:43.750 --> 35:47.493
[cell phone chimes]
Ooh, didn't expect that.

35:47.536 --> 35:49.364
DCFS tracked down
Makayla's family.

35:49.408 --> 35:52.454
Cousin's on the way.
- Oh, that's great.

35:52.498 --> 35:54.456
You know, it's your instincts
that got the case

35:54.500 --> 35:56.066
and protected her.

35:56.110 --> 35:57.155
It's good work.

35:57.198 --> 35:58.721
You could let it count
for something.

35:58.765 --> 36:00.114
- Eh.

36:00.158 --> 36:01.637
- What?

36:01.681 --> 36:03.422
- I don't know.
I was just thinking.

36:03.465 --> 36:05.119
- About what?

36:07.165 --> 36:09.079
- When we got pregnant.

36:11.778 --> 36:13.475
I'm a cop.

36:13.519 --> 36:15.303
I love being a cop.
I'm good at it.

36:15.347 --> 36:16.870
- Mm-hmm.

36:16.913 --> 36:19.568
- I didn't think I'd have
the instincts to be a mom too.

36:19.612 --> 36:22.267
And then what happened
happened.

36:22.310 --> 36:24.704
- No, you would've
been good at both.

36:26.836 --> 36:28.577
- You're always giving me
the benefit of the doubt.

36:28.621 --> 36:30.579
- No, I'm not.
I know you.

36:30.623 --> 36:32.233
You would've had instincts
for all of it.

36:32.277 --> 36:33.452
That's all.

36:33.495 --> 36:35.845
That's just how it is.

36:35.889 --> 36:38.674
- Yeah.

36:38.718 --> 36:40.720
Maybe it makes you better
at both.

36:43.331 --> 36:45.638
- Are we hanging tonight
or what?

36:45.681 --> 36:47.205
- I don't know.
Can you stand the monotony?

36:47.248 --> 36:48.554
- [laughs]

36:48.597 --> 36:52.166
Yeah, you know what?
About that, I spoke to Barkey.

36:52.210 --> 36:55.256
Apparently, that boat
was not his to sell.

36:55.300 --> 36:56.518
- [gasps]
He stole the boat?

36:56.562 --> 36:59.391
- No, he won it
in a not-so-legitimate parlay.

37:01.306 --> 37:02.481
He did steal that boat.

37:02.524 --> 37:04.744
He stole it.

37:04.787 --> 37:06.267
- I will meet you at the bar.

37:06.311 --> 37:08.356
I'm gonna wait with Makayla.
- All right.

37:08.400 --> 37:11.359
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

37:11.403 --> 37:18.410
<i>♪</i>

37:23.893 --> 37:25.591
- See, mine don't do it.

37:27.419 --> 37:30.813
Got all your stuff, okay?
So don't worry about that.

37:30.857 --> 37:32.772
Look who's here.
- Kathy!

37:34.948 --> 37:37.255
- Hi, I'm Kathy Ward.
- Hi.

37:37.298 --> 37:38.647
Kim Burgess.
- Good to meet you.

37:38.691 --> 37:40.388
- You too.
This is her stuff.

37:40.432 --> 37:41.433
- Okay.

37:41.476 --> 37:43.652
- And here's my card.

37:43.696 --> 37:46.786
You call if you need anything
or if you wanna keep in touch.

37:46.829 --> 37:50.180
- Thank you.
- Yeah.

37:50.224 --> 37:57.231
<i>♪</i>

38:02.802 --> 38:04.847
- All right, let's do this.

38:04.891 --> 38:07.850
Just rip the Band-Aid off.
- [chuckles]

38:07.894 --> 38:09.417
- What did the FBI offer you?

38:09.461 --> 38:12.290
- Hmm, okay.

38:13.334 --> 38:16.206
Joint level task force
with the HIG.

38:16.250 --> 38:19.427
All interrogations.
All high-level targets.

38:19.471 --> 38:20.646
- Sure.
Sure, sure, sure.

38:20.689 --> 38:22.822
Yeah, that sounds awesome.
- [laughs]

38:22.865 --> 38:25.564
- Is it good pay?
- It's great pay.

38:25.607 --> 38:27.305
Honestly, it made me
a little embarrassed

38:27.348 --> 38:28.567
about what we get paid.

38:28.610 --> 38:31.309
- Well, you'd probably
be really good at it.

38:31.352 --> 38:33.354
- Yeah, maybe.
I don't know.

38:33.398 --> 38:35.574
- You liked it out there,
right?

38:35.617 --> 38:38.881
- Uh...I don't know
if I liked it.

38:38.925 --> 38:41.797
I think it was just
what I needed at the time.

38:41.841 --> 38:44.409
- Okay, but you don't
need it now?

38:45.584 --> 38:46.976
- No, why?
You think I need it?

38:47.020 --> 38:48.587
Are you trying to tell me
I should take it?

38:48.630 --> 38:50.458
- No, uh...

38:50.502 --> 38:54.549
I'm saying that
it's a good job for a good cop.

38:59.554 --> 39:03.253
- You could tell me
you don't want me to take it.

39:03.297 --> 39:05.343
It was an option.

39:09.738 --> 39:13.612
- I want you to do
whatever you wanna do.

39:13.655 --> 39:16.354
I'm just practicing
self-preservation here.

39:19.444 --> 39:21.359
- The agent on the phone
said the only reason

39:21.402 --> 39:22.838
a good cop doesn't take
a job like this

39:22.882 --> 39:25.363
is 'cause they're scared,

39:25.406 --> 39:28.322
implying that
I'm afraid of change

39:28.366 --> 39:32.848
and I wanted to stay here
where it's safe.

39:32.892 --> 39:35.416
- So he's a dick.
- [laughs]

39:38.854 --> 39:41.553
I don't think that's why
I don't wanna take it.

39:43.685 --> 39:46.253
I don't wanna take it
because of you.

39:50.736 --> 39:52.781
I'm better...

39:52.825 --> 39:54.957
with you as my partner.

39:55.001 --> 39:59.266
You know, you, 21, with Voight.

39:59.309 --> 40:01.747
I know I'm better here.

40:02.922 --> 40:05.664
So I'm not gonna take it.

40:05.707 --> 40:10.364
<i>♪</i>

40:10.408 --> 40:11.887
- You sure?

40:11.931 --> 40:13.411
- Yeah.

40:15.630 --> 40:16.718
- All set.

40:16.762 --> 40:23.769
<i>♪</i>

40:29.383 --> 40:31.603
- He wasn't really wrong,
though, was he?

40:34.344 --> 40:37.783
You gain something.
You give something up.

40:43.049 --> 40:46.356
- Maybe, but...not always.

40:46.400 --> 40:52.014
<i>♪</i>

40:52.058 --> 40:53.494
- Ugh.

40:56.976 --> 40:58.717
It's been a long time

40:58.760 --> 41:00.719
since I saw you
as just my partner.

41:00.762 --> 41:02.111
Ugh.

41:02.155 --> 41:08.770
<i>♪</i>

41:51.726 --> 41:54.686
<i>[wolf howls]</i>
